KeyboardLayoutMapEntries.summary:
The entries read-only property
of the interface returns an array of a given object's
own enumerable property [key, value] pairs, in the same order as that
provided by a loop (the difference being
that a for-in loop enumerates properties in the prototype chain as well).
KeyboardLayoutMapEntries.value:
An array of the given KeyboardLayoutMap object's own enumerable property
[key, value] pairs.
